<br>
The good news is that as part of this patch, we've fixed the &quot;warp on flee&quot; bug that plagues many areas of the game. In some zones, NPCs will warp-off somewhere when they turn to flee. They tend to come back at nearly full health, usually leading a nice train behind them. They'll no longer warp when fleeing.<br>
<br>
-Gordon<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 One thing that I forgot to mention is that harmful DOTs will now report to the caster when they wear off the target. Furthermore, pets will report to their owner whenever *any* spell wears off of them. No more guessing involved. <br>
I believe that someone suggested it on the boards yesterday, and I said I'd take it to the team. Well the programmer who does things like that regularly reads the board here. He grabbed it and ran with it. <br>
<br>
The technology that lets us report when charm and fear wears off is what let us do this fairly easily. <br>
<br>
-Gordon<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
